==English==

===Etymology===
The surname may have two origins:
* from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|Dēorwine|gloss={{non-gloss definition|a given name}}}}, composed of {{m|ang|dēor|gloss=dear}} + {{m|ang|wine|gloss=friend}};
* habitational name from {{w|Darwen}} in Lancashire.

The city in Australia is named after [[w:Charles Darwin|Charles Darwin]].

